1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,935
Am I better than him?

2
00:00:00,935 --> 00:00:01,870
Am I less than him?

3
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:02,704
Am I richer?

4
00:00:02,704 --> 00:00:04,361
Am I more good-looking than her?

5
00:00:04,361 --> 00:00:07,723
These are the comparisons that always run
in people's minds.

6
00:00:07,723 --> 00:00:11,530
See, someone who wishes to be good-looking
is never happy within,

7
00:00:11,530 --> 00:00:13,227
because they're always comparing
themselves.

8
00:00:13,227 --> 00:00:15,390
I would never wish this upon your
daughters.

9
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:20,107
Someone who is beautiful within doesn't compare
their looks with another person, their content.

10
00:00:20,107 --> 00:00:22,764
you like white, you're only happy when you
see white,

11
00:00:22,764 --> 00:00:24,230
you're unhappy when you see black.

12
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:26,350
But if you like neither black nor white,

13
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,410
now you see the beauty in both of them.

14
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:31,281
When you have an image of what beauty is
like,

15
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,344
you are only happy with half of this
world.

16
00:00:33,344 --> 00:00:35,144
The other half cannot make you happy.

17
00:00:35,144 --> 00:00:38,024
If you like long hair, short hair makes
you unhappy.

18
00:00:38,024 --> 00:00:40,546
If you like neither, then you see the
beauty in both.

19
00:00:40,546 --> 00:00:43,577
But to you, half of it is beautiful, the
other half is ugly.

20
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:47,019
When you see ugly, and you keep doing that
until you see beauty.

21
00:00:47,019 --> 00:00:48,510
It brings you happiness, doesn't it?

22
00:00:48,510 --> 00:00:50,796
I don't need that, because I have found
beauty within.

23
00:00:50,796 --> 00:00:53,153
So show me anything and I'll be happy with
that.

24
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:55,702
Stop showing me anything, I'll be happy
with that.

25
00:00:55,702 --> 00:00:57,977
Unconditional happiness, that's what we
need.
